Josh,

The problem is

gas1 = gas2.

The Cantera MATLAB interface doesn&#39;t support object creation by 
assignment. The MATLAB object only contains a pointer (actually an 
integer) to a C++ object.  So this statement creates a copy of the 
pointer, with the result that both gas1 and gas2 point to the same C++ 
object.  To create two independent gases, you need to call IdealGsMix 
twice:

gas1 = IdealGasMix(&#39;gri30.xml&#39;);
gas2 = IdealGasMix(&#39;gri30.xml&#39;);


